01:18:58,280 --> 01:19:00,396
We checked on her room,
every night for three months.

731
01:19:00,520 --> 01:19:04,195
First night she slept was the night
that you busted in our front door.

732
01:19:04,360 --> 01:19:08,751
And I'll tell you what I'd do different,
count yourself dead at the outset.

733
01:19:08,880 --> 01:19:11,792
Accept that going in,
use it to your advantage.

734
01:19:13,360 --> 01:19:15,999
If you're not afraid, she can't hurt you.

735
01:19:39,400 --> 01:19:41,789
No money, no way to contact her.

736
01:19:42,800 --> 01:19:45,997
Must have went 80 on the way back,
straight through,

737
01:19:46,120 --> 01:19:47,997
didn't stop for nothing.

738
01:19:48,880 --> 01:19:52,270
When we got home,
she was waiting for us on the doorstep.

739
01:19:52,760 --> 01:19:56,594
Where is she now?
Some family, somewhere?

740
01:19:57,200 --> 01:20:00,351
Eddie said, "We're gonna burn her,"
and I said, "Okay."

741
01:20:02,360 --> 01:20:05,557
They did what I said for a while,
but then they stopped

742
01:20:06,800 --> 01:20:08,870
and started with the secrets.

743
01:20:09,640 --> 01:20:12,200
But they weren't really secrets, I guess,

744
01:20:12,800 --> 01:20:15,633
because I always knew
what they were thinking.

745
01:20:24,000 --> 01:20:27,629
- Don't leave me.
- It's okay, Maggie. I'll check on you later.

746
01:21:33,800 --> 01:21:36,792
I'm glad you're getting
the help you need, Daddy.

747
01:21:57,880 --> 01:21:58,915
Get somebody down here now.

748
01:21:59,120 --> 01:22:00,314
- Somebody call it in.
- Base, this is Sanchez.

749
01:22:00,920 --> 01:22:02,512
We're gonna need medical personnel
right away to the cafeteria...

750
01:22:15,800 --> 01:22:17,756
- Edward Sullivan...
- I know.

751
01:22:18,800 --> 01:22:20,870
Something I want you to hear.

752
01:22:21,840 --> 01:22:24,991
This came in this morning,
right about 2:00 a.m.

753
01:22:25,120 --> 01:22:26,792
You might wanna sit.

754
01:22:30,760 --> 01:22:34,196
...decide what to do with you
and your family, Michael.

755
01:22:35,240 --> 01:22:40,473
Every time I think about it,
a voice in my head says, "Kill them."

756
01:22:41,520 --> 01:22:42,839
Who is this?

757
01:22:43,600 --> 01:22:45,318
Just a little girl.

758
01:22:46,840 --> 01:22:50,037
- Up past her bedtime.
- Lilith?

759
01:22:55,240 --> 01:22:59,028
You were right. She did call Doug.
She used your cell phone.

760
01:23:00,760 --> 01:23:02,990
Took me a couple of extra days
to check your cell phone records,

761
01:23:03,120 --> 01:23:05,395
but that's what she's been using.

762
01:23:06,960 --> 01:23:10,430
- She's tearing me apart.
- You're not crazy, Emily. This is real.

763
01:23:10,560 --> 01:23:12,710
Edward said I have to kill her.

764
01:23:20,000 --> 01:23:21,479
I'll help you.

765
01:23:26,960 --> 01:23:28,996
Keep her at the house.

766
01:23:29,120 --> 01:23:31,395
Physically you're fine. How's the stress?

767
01:23:31,520 --> 01:23:33,511
I'm not sleeping.

768
01:23:33,640 --> 01:23:36,200
I was hoping you could
give me something.

769
01:23:38,000 --> 01:23:40,195
Take one of these, you'll sleep.

770
01:23:56,120 --> 01:23:57,155
Lily?

771
01:24:51,120 --> 01:24:52,155
What?

772
01:24:55,280 --> 01:24:56,713
Oh, my God.

773
01:26:08,920 --> 01:26:10,319
Who is this?

774
01:26:10,560 --> 01:26:13,120
Emily, it's Wayne,

775
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:15,515
I just got a call, Mike's dead.

776
01:26:16,000 --> 01:26:17,831
- No, he's...
- Listen, Em.

777
01:26:17,960 --> 01:26:20,030
They think he shot himself.

778
01:26:20,640 --> 01:26:24,189
- Emily? Em?
- No...

779
01:26:27,440 --> 01:26:30,910
Emily? Emily, are you okay?

780
01:26:44,600 --> 01:26:49,628
Get out of my house!

781
01:26:58,640 --> 01:27:00,517
Get out of my house!

782
01:27:08,120 --> 01:27:11,032
Don't yell at me!

783
01:27:37,640 --> 01:27:41,599
Emily, I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

784
01:27:41,720 --> 01:27:44,712
Can I come in so we can talk
and work it out?

785
01:27:49,640 --> 01:27:50,959
Emily?

786
01:27:52,200 --> 01:27:53,918
Stay away from me!

787
01:27:54,040 --> 01:27:58,591
Don't be mad. I said I was sorry.
I'll brush your hair for you.

788
01:27:58,720 --> 01:28:00,278
Stay away from me!

789
01:28:18,680 --> 01:28:23,435
No! No. No.

790
01:28:48,840 --> 01:28:52,674
Emily. Emily.

791
01:28:53,920 --> 01:28:57,754
We need to learn healthier ways
of resolving conflict, Emily.

792
01:29:01,640 --> 01:29:05,156
Most families
don't even know they have a problem

793
01:29:07,400 --> 01:29:09,118
until it's too late.

794
01:29:23,720 --> 01:29:27,030
What are you doing,
you silly pumpkinhead?

795
01:29:27,760 --> 01:29:30,877
You don't want me to come under there
and get you, do you?

796
01:29:31,000 --> 01:29:33,639
- No.
- I'm going to count to three.

797
01:29:35,040 --> 01:29:38,874
- One, two...
- No.

798
01:29:39,560 --> 01:29:43,030
Two and a half, two and three quarters,

799
01:29:44,680 --> 01:29:47,877
three. Here I come.

800
01:29:49,200 --> 01:29:53,034
- No! What do you want?
- What you wanted from your mother.

801
01:29:55,720 --> 01:29:58,075
I want you to love me.

802
01:30:00,760 --> 01:30:03,115
Okay. I will.

803
01:30:06,720 --> 01:30:08,312
Come tuck me in.

804
01:30:12,600 --> 01:30:14,318
Oh, my God.

805
01:30:21,200 --> 01:30:22,553
Emily.

806
01:31:06,160 --> 01:31:07,559
Chamomile.

807
01:31:12,680 --> 01:31:16,195
Maybe you should have it,
you look stressed.

808
01:31:17,800 --> 01:31:19,472
I'll have one later.

809
01:31:24,600 --> 01:31:28,036
I'm really sorry
that I let things get like this.

810
01:31:28,160 --> 01:31:31,232
- We'll do better from now on.
- We have to.

811
01:31:32,480 --> 01:31:34,550
Someone could get hurt.

812
01:31:36,800 --> 01:31:38,791
What should we do tomorrow?

813
01:31:40,280 --> 01:31:44,319
- Surprise me.
- I'm not so good at surprises.

814
01:31:44,840 --> 01:31:46,876
You're getting better.

815
01:34:00,040 --> 01:34:01,678
Everybody get out okay?

816
01:34:06,800 --> 01:34:09,439
Ma'am, anyone else inside? Yes or no?

817
01:34:17,560 --> 01:34:18,993
That was mean.

818
01:34:31,840 --> 01:34:35,515
You follow us downtown,
we'll find someplace for you to stay.

819
01:34:36,360 --> 01:34:38,271
Miss? You okay?

820
01:34:42,960 --> 01:34:44,313
I'm fine.

821
01:34:51,080 --> 01:34:54,038
Maybe we can find a hotel
with a swimming pool.

822
01:35:04,760 --> 01:35:08,719
- Where are we going?
- You said I should surprise you.

823
01:35:14,520 --> 01:35:16,397
She hated herself.

824
01:35:17,960 --> 01:35:19,837
And she hated you.

825
01:35:19,960 --> 01:35:23,669
They said it was an accident,
but you knew it wasn't.

826
01:35:23,800 --> 01:35:25,028
Your mother.

827
01:35:25,160 --> 01:35:27,833
That's why you never had
any kids of your own.

828
01:35:27,960 --> 01:35:30,315
That's what you're afraid of, isn't it?

829
01:35:30,440 --> 01:35:33,352
The part of you that's her.

830
01:35:34,680 --> 01:35:36,272
What are you?

831
01:35:44,240 --> 01:35:46,834
- Slow down!
- What the hell are you?

832
01:35:46,960 --> 01:35:50,873
You're upset, you shouldn't be driving.

833
01:36:06,960 --> 01:36:08,029
Mom.

834
01:36:14,560 --> 01:36:18,235
Mom, slow down, you're scaring me.

835
01:36:24,920 --> 01:36:27,195
Mom! Slow down, please!

836
01:36:31,480 --> 01:36:32,959
Look out!

837
01:36:35,400 --> 01:36:36,958
- It's not real.
- Yes, it is!

838
01:36:39,560 --> 01:36:42,074
It's not real!

839
01:37:03,240 --> 01:37:04,673
Are you scared?

840
01:37:10,280 --> 01:37:11,508
I'm not.

841
01:37:45,600 --> 01:37:47,033
I'm not afraid.

842
01:38:03,760 --> 01:38:05,239
Just die!

843
01:38:44,280 --> 01:38:48,398
No! No!

844
01:38:51,200 --> 01:38:52,997
No!

845
01:41:45,000 --> 01:41:50,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

846
01:42:49,000 --> 01:42:54,000
Upcoming jump scare (Minor)

